cui_parser_timestamp_format_help:
Format specifiers that are used by the Timestamp parser are:

  • '%a': Abbreviated weekday name, e.g. Thu
  • '%A': Full weekday name, e.g. Thursday
  • '%b': Abbreviated month name, e.g. Aug
  • '%B': Full month name, e.g. August
  • '%d': Day of the month, zero-padded (01-31), e.g. 03
  • '%e': Day of the month, space-padded ( 1-31), e.g. 3
  • '%f': Fractional seconds of time, e.g. .036
  • '%H': Hour in 24h format (00-23), e.g. 14
  • '%I': Hour in 12h format (01-12), e.g. 02
  • '%m': Month as a decimal number (01-12), e.g. 08
  • '%M': Minute (00-59), e.g. 55
  • '%p': AM or PM designation, e.g. PM
  • '%S': Second (00-61), e.g. 02
  • '%Y': Year, e.g. 2001
  • '%z': Timezone offset (1 min=1, 1 hour=100), e.g. +100
